 PERFORMING ARTS

 September 19 amp; 20 at Bharatiyam, IB 201 Salt Lake; 6 pm: Umang ? a programme of music, dance and dance-drama to be presented by the physically and mentally challenged: Rabindrasangeet by Arnab Majumder of Ganmarga Kendra, Karna ? a dance-drama choreographed by Priti Patel and to be staged by Anjika, and another dance-drama by Alakendu Bodh Niketan on September 19; and Odissi dance and dance-drama Bandhu by Pratibandhi Kalyan Kendra, Hooghly; Utsav Milan, a dance-drama choreographed by Nandini Sinha and to be staged by Arpan, and another dance-drama by Manovikas Kendra on September 20. 

 September 19 at Swabhumi; 6 pm: Bengali modern songs and Rabindrasangeet presented by Tanima Basu. 

 September 20 at Rabindra Sadan; 6 pm: In felicitation of Geeta Ghatak, the state government?s department of information and cultural affairs and Anandabroti present an evening of Tagore songs, duet reading and recitation . Participants include Abhirup Guha Thakurta, Pramita Mullick, Sreekanto Acharya, Swagatalakshmi Dasgupta, Debashis Roy Choudhury, Molly Debnath and Ishita Das Adhikari. Presenter: Subir Mitra. 

 September 24 at Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Vivekananda Hall; 6 pm: Charcha: Marga Sangit - Bishnupur Gharana. Short discourse by Subhas Chowdhury; Amiya Ranjan Bandopadhyay (khayal) with Manilal Nag (sitar) and Samar Saha (tabla). 

